<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,1628,1871]" box="[199,1319,1664,1692]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1664,1691]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[663,762,1665,1691]" name="Portugal" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: one province (Algarve) (also Dyte unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,1628,1871]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1701,1727]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Ecology.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[344,439,1701,1727]" name="Portugal" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Portugal</collectingCountry>
only recorded from a brackish marsh. Indeed, also in the rest of Europe, this species displays a distinct preference for halophilous habitats like saltmarshes and brackish marshes in coastal regions or nearby river deltas (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[374,509,1773,1799]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[151,1436,1628,1871]" box="[199,631,1808,1835]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1808,1835]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
